parameters:
\SE[2]It's not just beautiful places, huh... It feels like
struggling with flutter kicks in an invisible underwater
place, giving off a swan-like emotion...!

\SE[6] The most troublesome are the devout believers of
absolute affirmation...

\SE[13]This is the Trap Dungeon. Various traps are waiting
for you! \SE[12]Let's conquer them little by little through
trial and error!

\SE[2]Actually, I was just asking for a test play from
someone else...

\SE[4]Mama...!! \.Laura is with you too! \!\SE[15]I wonder
if both of you were helping out.

\SE[14]No, I asked for a test play but this time I only
reached out to Lunaroa...

\SE[2]You can even create your own companion character
yourself. \!\SE[1]There are no particular restrictions,
except that it starts at Level 1, so if you have unique
preferences, you can do something like this...

\SE[51]Even though it was just a test play, I got really
into it... \SE[10]Since I went through all that trouble, can
I introduce the strongest party that I came up with to
everyone?

\SE[11]Let me explain from the left. First is Part 1 Laura.
\SE[10]She excels in high speed and support. Her attack
power is a bit modest, but she holds great potential.

\SE[21]The sight of her earnestly strengthening me...
\!\SE[40]Even during battles, it's troubling how she
unintentionally cheers me up...!

\SE[22]I'm 'Laura'! \!\SE[0]I'm not sure what I can do,
but... \!\SE[100]I'll do my best not to hold everyone
back...!

\SE[28]So, um... \SE[91]I... I like my childhood friend
Lunaroa... \SE[21]In the game Yurisene, we're going to get
married someday...!

\SE[22]M-Mou... Laura! \!\SE[21]Even if you don't say that,
I already know...!

\SE[12]N-Next, let's move on! Part 2 Laura!! \SE[10]She can
use Dual Wielding and boasts high DPS as the main firepower!
Her appearance is just like The strongest Laura I came up
with...!

\SE[32]To help me, she carries my sword... \!\SE[30]Moving
forward with both 'strength' and 'weakness'...
\!\SE[51]Sigh... It's so precious. Just this makes me want
to cry a little...

\SE[2]I'm 'Laura'. \!\SE[18]I won't hesitate anymore. I will
become stronger to help Lunaroa...!

\SE[12]Instead of being someone who is protected by
Lunaroa... I want to become someone who stands alongside
Lunaroa...!
\SE[51]Kyaa!! So cool!! \!\SE[29]Hurry, help me!! Hold me!!
\SE[12]I wonder if Laura would faint if she saw this...

\SE[11]Next is the last one! \.The childhood 'Laura'...!
\!\SE[10]She may not have high attack power, but she has
excellent 'healing abilities'! \.She can be considered the
'core' of the team...!

\SE\SE[10]I deliberately keep my defense low...! \SE[10]Even
during battles, I always have this feeling of I have to
protect...! and it makes me feel warm and fuzzy inside!

\SE[15]I'm 'Laura'! Let me know if you get hurt! I'll heal
you right away! \SE[46]I'm still small, but I hope I can be
of help!

\SE[9]When Lunaroa loses to a boss and gets all worried,
it's my turn to shine! \SE[46]I comfort her by saying Good
girl, good girl ♥ and cheering her on with Do your best ♥!

\SE[7]W-Well... as long as you're enjoying yourself, that's
what matters. \!\SE[2]What are your plans for after this?

\SE\SE[10]I've saved up money from the 'quests', so I'm
going to enhance Laura's equipment even further in the
'city'...! \!\SE[10]With this, we should be able to improve
our farming efficiency even more!

\SE[2]Well, if it's Lunaroa right now, maybe I can say it...
\!\SE[43]You should try going to the Church Basement. I
think there will be a special fun event that will occur.

\SE[11]The 'Church Basement', huh! I got it...! Let's go
check it out! \SE[10]Alright...! Let's go, Laura...!

\SE\SE[10]I hope both of you enjoy it. \!\SE[10]Let's play
together someday...!

\SE[16]Mom... You seemed really happy! \SE[0]But you seemed
a little strange!

\SE[6]You're really obsessed, aren't you...? \SE[9]Are you
even making legal drugs?

\SE[68]Legal drugs... Well, there's a saying that goes
something like how to produce brain drugs in creative works,
so maybe it's not that far off...? \!\SE[51]

\SE[4]Well... never mind. \SE[0]The debug is up ahead.
\SE[0]Let's keep going with this momentum and see how it
goes!
